  "A city's average monthly temperature is modeled by T(m) = 22 cos(πm/6) + 58°F, where m = 0 is January. A construction company can only pour concrete when T ≥ 47°F. During which months (starting from m = 0) is the temperature first below 47°F?": "",
  "m = 4 (May)": "",
  "m = 10 (November)": "",
  "m = 6 (July)": "",
  "m = 8 (September)": "",
  "Set T = 47: cos(πm/6) = −1/2, so πm/6 = 2π/3, giving m = 4. But cos decreases then, so T < 47 begins after m = 4. Solving more carefully: T drops below 47 at m = 8 (the second crossing going into cold months).": "",
  "A Ferris wheel of radius 20 m (center 22 m above ground) has h(t) = 20 sin(πt/30 − π/2) + 22. A photographer wants to snap a photo when the rider is exactly 32 m high. At what first positive time does this happen?": "",
  "t = 10 s": "",
  "t = 25 s": "",
  "t = 15 s": "",
  "t = 20 s": "",
  "Set 20 sin(πt/30 − π/2) + 22 = 32, so sin(πt/30 − π/2) = 1/2. Then πt/30 − π/2 = π/6, giving t = 20 s.": "",
  "The depth of water in a harbor is d(t) = 4.5 cos(πt/6.2) + 8 meters, where t is hours after midnight. A cargo ship needs at least 10 m of water. At what time is the depth first insufficient (drops below 10 m)?": "",
  "About 3.1 hours after midnight": "",
  "About 6.2 hours after midnight": "",
  "Never — depth always exceeds 10 m": "",
  "About 2.3 hours after midnight": "",
  "Set 4.5 cos(πt/6.2) + 8 = 10, so cos(πt/6.2) = 4/9 ≈ 0.444. Then πt/6.2 = arccos(0.444) ≈ 1.11, giving t ≈ 2.19 hours, approximately 2.3 hours.": "",
  "A thermostat cycles room temperature as T(t) = 2 sin(πt/30) + 70°F, where t is in minutes. The heating kicks in when T drops to 68°F. At what time after t = 0 does heating first start?": "",
  "t = 15 min": "",
  "t = 35 min": "",
  "t = 210/π ≈ 66.8 min": "",
  "t = 210/π · (7/6) ≈ 37 min": "",
  "Set 2 sin(πt/30) + 70 = 68, so sin(πt/30) = −1. Then πt/30 = 3π/2, giving t = 45 min. However let's recheck: sin(πt/30) = −1 at πt/30 = 3π/2 → t = 45 min.": "",
  "A seasonal sales model is S(w) = 1500 sin(πw/26) + 5000 units, where w is the week of the year. When do sales first exceed 6000 units?": "",
