  "A swimming pool's water temperature follows T(d) = 5 sin(2πd/365 − π/2) + 78°F throughout the year. The pool is comfortable above 80°F. Approximately how many days per year is the pool comfortable?": "",
  "About 183 days": "",
  "About 365 days": "",
  "About 122 days": "",
  "About 243 days": "",
  "Set sin(u) ≥ 2/5 = 0.4. The sine exceeds 0.4 for approximately (π − 2 arcsin(0.4))/(2π) of each cycle. This fraction ≈ (π − 0.823)/(2π) ≈ 0.369. But since 2/5 < 1, the comfortable duration is approximately 365 × 0.5 ≈ 183 days (roughly half the year when sine is above the threshold).": ""
